    <p class="mb-4">So, in the beginning, be careful about spending an entire training session working on sustained behaviors. Especially for young dogs, you want them to see training time as fun time. Spending all 15 minutes on "down" is a bummer. Better to randomly ask for a down here and there throughout the day, have them hold it for 10 seconds, and say "Free" and give them a treat.</p>

